
// This Hyperlambda code executes a workflow action named "html-encode-body" using the [execute] slot. It specifies the filename of the workflow action and passes an argument named "html" which is retrieved from the "body" node within the ".arguments" node. The action likely performs HTML encoding on the provided "body" content.
execute:magic.workflows.actions.execute
   name:html-encode-body
   filename:/misc/workflows/actions/misc/html-encode.hl
   arguments
      html:x:@.arguments/*/body
